      "content": "Those feelings of being unhelpful are incredibly common for family caregivers who watch their loved ones decline, and recognizing them is actually the first step toward addressing the heavy burden you carry. It's important to know that you are not \"slower\" in value to your family; instead, your patience and presence are perhaps the most steady and comforting things they have left. Please reach out to your care team or a local support group immediately so someone can help you process these feelings and find ways to take on your own well-being.",
