      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are absolutely right that their exhaustion is a tangible reality, and your self-awareness about potentially adding to their burden shows immense respect for them. This isn't a lack of love but a wise recognition that their well-being requires you to reign in your own role to make space for their own support system. Speaking with a therapist or your medical team about redistributing tasks could help lighten your load so you can be present without draining them further.",
      "source": "target",
